  "prompt": "What business model does olx use?",
  "response": "OLX primarily operates on a **classified advertising business model**, which connects buyers and sellers directly on its platform. Here\u2019s a breakdown of how it works:\n\n1. **Free Listings**: OLX allows users to post ads for free to list items, services, or properties they want to sell or rent. This attracts a large user base.\n\n2. **Paid Features**: While basic listings are free, OLX offers optional **premium features** for a fee, such as:\n   - Highlighting ads to make them more visible.\n   - Bumping ads to the top of search results.\n   - Adding extra images or detailed descriptions.\n\n3. **Advertising Revenue**: OLX generates revenue through **display ads** and **sponsored listings** posted by businesses or individuals who want greater visibility.\n\n4. **Local Focus**: OLX operates in multiple countries and tailors its platform to local markets, focusing on user needs and preferences in each region.\n\n5. **No Inventory or Transaction Fees**: Unlike e-commerce platforms, OLX does not hold inventory or facilitate payments directly. It acts as a marketplace for peer-to-peer transactions, which keeps its operational costs relatively low.\n\nThis model allows OLX to scale globally while maintaining a simple and user-friendly platform.",
